<br>
The stupid thing is that aggro wasn't broken in the first place.  Before this patch I still got aggro and got pummeled if I wasn't careful, I still had to control my damage and use concussion and be cautious.  Maybe aggro was broken for rangers, but it sure wasn't broken for us....  Now it's broken, but instead of being broken in that we can do too much damage without fear of aggro, we can't do any damage without fear of aggro.<br>
<br>
Why is it when they try to fix something they always WAY overcompensate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mythal>Mythal</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/03 7:39:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25912.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mythal.com/images/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro</span><hr size=1> Because it's planned that way to force us to accept nerfs?<br>
<br>
Here's an example.<br>
<br>
You can do 100 damage pre-patch, with no agro.<br>
You can do 10 damage post-patch, with no agro.<br>
People bitch about the nerf!<br>
VI listens attentively to their customers.<br>
VI makes an announcement &quot;We broke it, we'll fix it in 24 hours&quot;.<br>
A second patch later, you can do 80 damage, with no agro.<br>
People rejoice.<br>
<br>
End result? You still lost 20% of damage you were able to do before (which is what VI's plan was from the beginning), but now you're not bitching. In fact, you're actually happy and have the fuzzy feeling that VI is, in fact, listening to you!<br>
<br>
